00:09:32.410 --> 00:09:34.250
And so those are fascinating,
the ones

00:09:34.250 --> 00:09:35.370
that you don't expect.

00:09:35.370 --> 00:09:39.870
Now, those are fascinating
because those are peculiar.

00:09:39.870 --> 00:09:41.800
Maths is intuitive.

00:09:41.800 --> 00:09:43.590
And I want people to
understand that.

00:09:43.590 --> 00:09:45.410
Maths is an intuitive subject.

00:09:45.410 --> 00:09:48.000
What you believe to be
true, more often than

00:09:48.000 --> 00:09:49.495
not, actually is true.

00:09:49.495 --> 00:09:51.340
And that's how maths work.

00:09:51.340 --> 00:09:55.530
Mathematicians are not just
working through the steps.

00:09:55.530 --> 00:09:57.030
They are actually
making creative

00:09:57.030 --> 00:09:58.915
leaps, creative jumps.

00:09:58.915 --> 00:10:00.340
This is how it should work.

00:10:00.340 --> 00:10:02.640
This is how it should
be, so now I have to

00:10:02.640 --> 00:10:04.680
prove that it is.

00:10:04.680 --> 00:10:08.570
So you're using your intuition
to guide you.

00:10:08.570 --> 00:10:13.160
So the majority of maths is
intuitive in that sense.

00:10:13.160 --> 00:10:16.520
So when you get the
counter-intuitive ones, that's

00:10:16.520 --> 00:10:19.190
why mathematicians like
talking about them.

00:10:19.190 --> 00:10:21.650
I don't want to give people
the wrong idea that that's

00:10:21.650 --> 00:10:22.930
